timepart_perf - Performance benchmark for TRUNCATE time partition unique checks

Overview
--------
Measures the overhead of cross-shard unique index enforcement on TRUNCATE
time partitions.  Creates a daily partition with 8 shards, populates each
shard, then runs UPDATE workloads under three configurations:

  off         partition_unique disabled (baseline)
  on          partition_unique enabled with table read locks
  on-nolocks  partition_unique enabled, table read locks skipped

Each phase repopulates the shards to identical initial state before running,
so all three configurations execute the same workload.  Phases are randomly
ordered per iteration to neutralise cache-warming effects.

Parameters
----------
Override on the make command line, e.g.:
  make timepart_perf ROWS_PER_SHARD=1000 NWORKERS=4 ITERATIONS=5

  ROWS_PER_SHARD  Rows inserted per shard (default: 10000)
  NRANGES         Number of non-overlapping row ranges / max workers (default: 8)
  NWORKERS        Parallel writers (default: NRANGES)
  ITERATIONS      Benchmark repetitions (default: 3)
  TXN_SIZE        Rows per transaction (default: 10)
  D_SIZE          Bytes for randomblob() filler column (default: 16)
  DEBUG_TRACE     1=enable partition_unique_debug tunable and collect detailed
                  per-counter stats; 0=skip debug counters (default: 1)

Running
-------
Single node:
  cd tests && make timepart_perf

With custom parameters:
  make timepart_perf ROWS_PER_SHARD=100 NWORKERS=2 ITERATIONS=1 TXN_SIZE=1

Docker cluster (3 nodes):
  Create a run script:
    #!/bin/bash
    cd /comdb2/tests
    TESTDIR=/tmp/dhtest/$RANDOM
    trap "cp -r $TESTDIR /common/timepart_perf_logs" EXIT
    make CLUSTER="m1 m2 m3" SKIP_COPY_EXE=1 TESTDIR=$TESTDIR timepart_perf

  Then run:
    cd tests/docker
    ./runit -s <repo_root> -n 3 -f <path_to_run_script>

Output
------
Per-iteration timing line:
  iter 0 (off->on): off=50ms  on=55ms  on-nolocks=52ms

Summary table with totals, per-row averages, and % change vs off:

                                        off           on   on vs off   on-nolocks   nolocks vs off
  total time (ms)                     12345        13456         +9%        13200            +6%
  deadlocks                              10           15        +50%           14           +40%
  lock waits                            100          150        +50%          145           +45%
  total lock requests               500000       700000        +40%       680000           +36%

When DEBUG_TRACE=1, additional rows appear:
  lock reqs deadlocked txns            ...
  cross-shard lock requests            ...
  delayed key add calls                ...
  cross-shard unique checks            ...

Timeout: 30 minutes (set in Makefile).
